cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper proposes the use of deep radiomic features (DRFs) extracted from MRI scans to predict survival outcome of recurrent glioblastoma patients. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and random forest (RF) classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as RF classification, which suggests the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging and radiomics, which could fall under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
